race.comment: KIMBERLEY ROSE (4) showed good improvement second-up when out to the mile on the Scarpside at Pinjarra last time out. Third-up now and gets out to a more suitable trip for her. Ticks plenty of boxes off the inside draw and can go one better this time around. ROUNDABOUT GLORY (7) missed last start when setting the tempo, being caught late in the race. Up in trip again now but that doesn't look an issue and he has the speed to get across from an outside barrier. Down in weight here and can continue his strong run of form. OUR NEMESIS (1) led and won two back over the mile at Pinjarra before stepping up to Saturday grade and being outclassed. Drawn out, but has the speed to roll across and he looks well placed back to this grade. PLANET CASH (3) was too good over the mile on the Scarpside last start beating KIMBERLEY ROSE. Can repeat the dose. SUPER ROMANI (2) has claims after closing strongly last start.
